SIMPLE: subjection
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subjection
<hw>Sub*jec"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>subjectio</ets>: cf. OF. <ets>subjection</ets>, F.
<ets>subj⟦eacute⟧tion</ets>. See <er>Subject</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of subjecting, or of bringing under the
dominion of another; the act of subduing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The conquest of the kingdom, and <qex>subjection</qex> of the
rebels.</q> <rj><qau>Sir M. Hale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being subject, or under the power,
control, and government of another; a state of obedience or
submissiveness; <as>as, the safety of life, liberty, and property
depends on our <ex>subjection</ex> to the laws</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧To be
bound under <xex>subjection</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Likewise, ye wives, be in <qex>subjection</qex> to your own
husbands.</q> <rj><qau>1 Peter iii. 1.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Because the <qex>subjection</qex> of the body to the will is by
natural necessity, the <qex>subjection</qex> of the will unto God
voluntary, we stand in need of direction after what sort our wills and
desires may be rightly conformed to His.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subjectist</ent>⟦br⟧
